This paper discusses the use of Big Spectrum Data in cognitive wireless networking, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper focuses on wireless networking. The second likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper discusses data analytics. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper mentions the use of algorithms. The fourth likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses the challenges of handling large amounts of data. The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper mentions the use of sensors and data generated by mobile phones.
